# Frontend Environment Variables

# ============================================================================
# API Configuration
# ============================================================================

# API Base URL - Configure based on your deployment scenario:
#
# IMPORTANT: The frontend container now uses a simple static file server (serve)
# without proxy capabilities. API routing MUST be handled by your external
# reverse proxy server (nginx, Apache, Traefik, etc.).
#
# Scenario 1: External reverse proxy (RECOMMENDED for production)
# - Your proxy server routes /api/* requests to backend:8000
# - Frontend uses relative path so browser requests go through your proxy
# - Example proxy config:
#   location /api { proxy_pass http://backend:8000; }
#   location / { proxy_pass http://frontend:3000; }
VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api/v1
#
# Scenario 2: Direct connection to backend (Docker network)
# - Frontend container connects directly to backend container
# - Backend must be on same Docker network with hostname 'backend'
# - IMPORTANT: You must configure CORS in backend to allow frontend origin
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://backend:8000/api/v1
#
# Scenario 3: Direct connection to backend (external host)
# - Frontend connects to backend on specific IP/hostname
# - Useful for development or multi-server deployments
# - IMPORTANT: You must configure CORS in backend to allow frontend origin
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.10:8000/api/v1
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://medve.lan:8000/api/v1
#
# Scenario 4: Development with Vite proxy
# - Uses relative path, vite.config.ts configures proxy
# - Vite dev server handles proxying to backend during development
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api/v1

